			 <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="http://www1.uwindsor.ca">Home</a> / <a href="/odette/undergraduate-programs">Undergraduate Programs</a> / <a href="/odette/areas-of-study">Areas of Study</a> / <a href="/odette/accounting-area">Accounting</a> / <a href="/odette/cpa-pathway" class="active">CPA Pathway</a></div>                        <h1 class="title">Odette CPA Pathway</h1>
                        
                        			 <div id="node-1397" class="node node-type-page"><div class="node-inner">

  
  

  <div class="content">
    <h3>
	Your pathway to becoming a CPA begins here!</h3>
<p>Whether you are a business or non-business university graduate, a career-changer, or an internationally-educated student, this program is designed for you!</p>
<p>The unique Odette CPA Pathway provides students who already hold a four-year bachelor&rsquo;s degree the opportunity to complete the requirements for a professional accounting designation within four semesters (approximately 16 months) and without having to earn a second degree.&nbsp; Students holding three-year degrees can also complete this program &ndash; but may require a slightly longer timeline.</p>
<p>The following seven steps contain important information and make it easy for you to register.</p>
<p>1) <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Contact Odette to discuss your interest in becoming a CPA</span></p>
<p>Contact Prof. Jim Stevens, Odette Director of Professional Accounting Programs to discuss the program and find out how it fits your ambitions.</p>
<p class="rteindent1"><strong><a href="/odette/jim-stevens">Prof. Jim Stevens</a></strong><br />
	Director of Professional Accounting Programs<br />
	Odette School of Business<br />
	Room: OB 318B<br />
	Telephone: 519-253-3000 extension 3114<br />
	Facsimile: 519-973-7073<br />
	E-mail: <a href="mailto:stevenz@uwindsor.ca?subject=Odette%20CPA%20Pathway">stevenz@uwindsor.ca</a></p>
<p>2) <u>Documentation Required by Odette</u></p>
<p>Provide Odette with an unofficial transcript for an initial evaluation and creation of a tentative individualized education plan that works for you.&nbsp; Feel free to drop off your transcript in person or use the contact information provided in Step 1.</p>
<p>We will also require the information that the Institute will provide in Step 6 below to finalize your Odette CPA Pathway.</p>
<p>3)&nbsp; <u>Apply for Admission to the University of Windsor</u></p>
<p>Begin the application process at the University of Windsor (UWindsor) by enrolling in the appropriate Odette program specified in your individualized education plan.</p>
<p><a href="/registrar/how-to-apply" target="_blank"><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 85, 149);"><font color="#b2bb1e">&gt;&gt; </font></span></strong><strong>Apply to UWindsor</strong></a></p>
<p><em>Important note: Admission to UWindsor is selective and based on your educational background.&nbsp; You must be granted admittance before continuing the remaining steps.</em></p>
<p><em>To allow for completion of the admission process and to ensure priority registration in classes, students intending to follow the preferred sequencing are strongly encouraged to apply for admission by May 31.&nbsp; While we welcome and will process all applications, we are unable to guarantee class registrations for those granted admission with other start dates or who apply&nbsp; after May 31 for a September start.</em></p>
<p>4) <u>Register in your Courses at Odette</u></p>
<p>After enrolling at UWindsor, log in to <a href="http://my.uwindsor.ca" target="_blank">my.UWindsor.ca</a> to register for the specific business courses outlined in your individualized education plan.&nbsp; <a href="http://www1.uwindsor.ca/odette/system/files/CPA-Pathway-Preferred-Schedule-revised-19-Sep-13.pdf" target="_blank">Click here to review the preferred sequencing for CPA Pathway courses</a>.</p>
<p><a href="http://my.uwindsor.ca" target="_blank"><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 85, 149);"><font color="#b2bb1e">&gt;&gt; </font></span></strong><strong>Register for your courses</strong></a></p>
<p>5) <u>Exchange of Information between Odette and CPA Ontario</u></p>
<p>Complete the form authorizing Odette and <a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca" target="_blank">CPA Ontario</a> to share and discuss information related to your application.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 85, 149);"><font color="#b2bb1e">&gt;&gt; </font></span></strong><a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca/Forms/1008page14599.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Authorization Form</strong></a></p>
<p>6) <u>Documentation Required by the CPA Ontario</u></p>
<p>Initiate a transcript assessment with <a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca" target="_blank">CPA Ontario</a>.&nbsp; You will need to provide the Authorization Form from Step 5, and proof of admission to UWindsor from Step 3.</p>
<p><a href="/odette/system/files/Odette%20CA%20Pathway%20Preliminary%20Evaluation%20form.pdf" target="_blank"><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 85, 149);"><font color="#b2bb1e">&gt;&gt; </font></span></strong></a><a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca/Forms/1008page14081.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Odette CPA Pathway Preliminary Evaluation</strong></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca" target="_blank">CPA Ontario</a> will perform a preliminary evaluation of your unofficial degree(s) documents and determine course exemptions and courses needed to meet CPA Ontario&#39;s 51 credit-hour requirement.&nbsp; This preliminary evaluation will be shared with Odette and become part of your unique Odette CPA Pathway.&nbsp; The fee for this preliminary evaluation is:</p>
<ul>
<li>
		Ontario University Transcripts = $50 (plus applicable taxes)</li>
<li>
		Canadian Non-Ontario University Transcripts = $100 (plus applicable taxes)</li>
<li>
		International University Transcripts = $480 (plus applicable taxes).&nbsp; Most of this fee will be applied to the CPA Ontario&#39;s CPA Student registration fee if registration takes place within five years of the preliminary evaluation date.</li>
</ul>
<p>Make sure you maintain an overall minimum B- grade point average in all of your required CPA courses (the calculation of this overall GPA will also include any CPA-recognized courses that were completed during your undergraduate studies at a Canadian university and were confirmed in your preliminary evaluation).</p>
<p>7) <u>I&rsquo;ve completed my Odette CPA Pathway!&nbsp; What now?</u></p>
<p>Your next step is to officially register with <a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca" target="_blank">CPA Ontario</a> as a CPA student by completing the registration form and paying the application fee, assuming that you are otherwise eligible.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 85, 149);"><font color="#b2bb1e">&gt;&gt; </font></span></strong><a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca/Forms/1008page2546.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>CPA Student Registration Form</strong></a></p>
<p>You must also provide <a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca" target="_blank">CPA Ontario</a> with:</p>
<ul>
<li>
		Official UWindsor transcripts showing successful completion of the required courses in your Odette CPA Pathway.</li>
<li>
		Official transcripts from any other recognized degree-granting institution(s), as needed, to verify the Odette CPA Pathway course exemptions (ie. official verification of the preliminary evaluation used to determine the courses included in your unique pathway established in Step 2).</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>For additional information, please visit the CPA Ontario &quot;Odette CPA Pathway&quot; webpage <a href="http://www.cpaontario.ca/Admissions/OdetteCPAPathway/1014page13852.aspx" target="_blank">here</a>.</strong></p>
  </div>

  
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
